                            <comment id="17768350" author="jira-bot" created="Sun, 24 Sep 2023 07:52:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit dc56b362fb4615afc8bc14803bfb9dbe3651a3ba in httpcomponents-client&apos;s branch refs/heads/&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HTTPCLIENT-2300&quot; title=&quot;AbstractCharDataConsumer throws java.nio.charset.MalformedInputException for an URI that SimpleResponseConsumer can handle&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HTTPCLIENT-2300&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HTTPCLIENT-2300&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; from Oleg Kalnichevski&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=httpcomponents-client.git;h=dc56b362f&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=httpcomponents-client.git;h=dc56b362f&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HTTPCLIENT-2300&quot; title=&quot;AbstractCharDataConsumer throws java.nio.charset.MalformedInputException for an URI that SimpleResponseConsumer can handle&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HTTPCLIENT-2300&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HTTPCLIENT-2300&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: AbstractCharResponseConsumer to use UTF-8 by default if a charset has not been explicitly specified by the Content-Type&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17768351" author="olegk" created="Sun, 24 Sep 2023 07:54:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jkmlee&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jkmlee&quot;&gt;jkmlee&lt;/a&gt; Please review / test the proposed fix:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/httpcomponents-client/compare/5.2.x...HTTPCLIENT-2300&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/httpcomponents-client/compare/5.2.x...HTTPCLIENT-2300&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Oleg&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17768380" author="jkmlee" created="Sun, 24 Sep 2023 12:10:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=olegk&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;olegk&quot;&gt;olegk&lt;/a&gt; The fix (changing AbstractCharResponseConsumer&apos;s default charset from UTF_8 to US_ASCII) works.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But it also causes the response body retrieved by AbstractCharResponseConsumer to be different from that retrieved by SimpleResponseConsumer because SimpleBody&apos;s default charset is still US_ASCII.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Somehow, &lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/lang/String.html#String-byte:A-java.nio.charset.Charset-&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;String(byte[] bytes, Charset charset)&lt;/a&gt; is able to create a string from an UTF_8 byte array even if US_ASCII is the specified charset, although the non-ASCII characters become corrupted in the resulting string.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If the byte stream to char stream conversion code in HttpCore is not able to handle an UTF_8 byte stream as an US_ASCII byte stream, should this fix also update the default charset of other classes in the org.apache.hc.client5.http.async.methods package (i.e. SimpleBody and AbstractCharPushConsumer) to ensure that their behavior is consistent?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17768381" author="jkmlee" created="Sun, 24 Sep 2023 12:13:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching &quot;utf8_content_without_charset.html&quot; for reference. This is the UTF-8 content retrieved using curl from &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.videolan.org/vlc/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://www.videolan.org/vlc/&lt;/a&gt;. The headers look like the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
